          "type": "faq",
          "settings": {
            "question": "How do I get the perfect bra fit?",
            "answer": "<p>Each Shapermint bra includes a size calculator and a detailed size chart to help you choose the right fit. For extra guidance, use our <a href=\"https://shapermint.com/pages/bra-size-calculator\">Bra Size Calculator</a> to discover your best size in each of our best sellers! Our<strong>soft everyday bras for all-day wear</strong>are specifically designed as<strong>bras that don't dig in</strong>, featuring smooth edges and flexible materials. If you're between sizes and prefer a roomier fit, we recommend sizing up for extra comfort.</p>"
          }
        },
        "faq_NcriAY": {
          "type": "faq",
          "settings": {
            "question": "Are your bras affordable without sacrificing quality?",
            "answer": "<p>Absolutely! Our<strong>affordable comfortable bras</strong>prove that you don't need to spend a fortune for superior comfort and support. These<strong>budget-friendly supportive bras </strong>use high-quality materials and thoughtful design, at prices that work for every budget.</p>"
          }
        },
        "faq_QTqmki": {
          "type": "faq",
          "settings": {
            "question": "Can I machine wash my bras?",
            "answer": "<p>Yes, but with proper care! To help your bras last longer, always place them in a lingerie bag before tossing them into the machine. Choose a gentle cycle with cold water, and skip the fabric softener, as it can damage the material and reduce stretch. Always air dry instead of using a dryer to preserve shape and support. Read our guide on <a href=\"https://store.shapermint.com/blogs/news/how-to-wash-your-bras\">how to machine-wash your bra</a> for detailed care tips.</p>"
          }
        },
        "faq_q6RdAD": {
          "type": "faq",
          "settings": {
            "question": "Can I put my bras in the dryer?",
            "answer": "<p>It’s best to skip the dryer! High heat can break down the elasticity and structure of your bra, reducing support and shortening its lifespan. Instead, lay your bra flat on a towel or hang it to air dry. This helps preserve the shape, stretch, and smoothing power you love.</p>"
          }
        }
